This paper discusses improvements to the IEEE 802.11ac standard for wireless local area networks (WLANs), which falls under the category of networked and internet technologies (cs.NI). The paper also discusses queuing mechanisms and channel usage, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed decoupled scheduling mechanism also involves system-level optimization (cs.SY) and potential security implications (cs.CR).
